<br />You should use more than 1 emulator to test your code. You can use your favorite one more often, but from time to time you should test in other emulators too, and you should include the most accurate ones (Nintendulator and Nestopia) in that group. If you are using Linux or Mac OS you should still try to run those emulators, even if you have to use Wine or a virtual machine. Even if runs too slow, you'll still be able to catch bugs.</div>

