<br />Would code like this work if I wanted the loop to run again AFTER the NMI is done? So that it only runs as fast as the refresh?
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Loop:<br />&nbsp; JSR Player1ControllerRead<br />&nbsp; LDA #$FF<br />EndLoop:<br />&nbsp; BNE EndLoop<br />&nbsp; JMP Loop<br />NMI:<br />&nbsp; LDA $2002<br />&nbsp; LDA #$00<br />&nbsp; STA $2003&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; set the low byte &#40;00&#41; of the RAM address<br />&nbsp; LDA #$02<br />&nbsp; STA $4014&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; set the high byte &#40;02&#41; of the RAM address, start the transfer<br />&nbsp; LDA #$00&nbsp; &nbsp;;No scroll?<br />&nbsp; STA $2005<br />&nbsp; STA $2005<br />&nbsp; RTI<br /></div></div>

